Funding Gap; 6,785,020 Shs. iv) PROJECT DURATION Twelve ( 12 ) Months.
(I) Back ground information; Richard Kyambadde is a youth who has got access to a vast piece of family land and has got a plan of putting this land to use by engaging it to profitable Agriculture production. The plan is to start with land clearance which will be followed with Maize production for the proceeding two seasons and eventually the area will be used for Pineapple and Beans growing at three and Two acreage respectively.
(II) Problem statement; Presently, there is a rampant problem of Land grabbing especially for land which is found laying idle or underutilized so Richard has realized that to safeguard the family land against such a possibility and the accompanying problems, and from the fact that the food prices are increasing and almost doubling and yet the Christians are almost going Hungry, it has been realized to be wise to put this land to Farming as a Business in order to tap the readily available market for the food stuffs in the country and even in the neighboring countries as well as saving the lives of Members of the Bride of Christ around the world Church community by giving them maize at a relatively lower costs than what other shops charge .
(III) Project beneficiaries and benefits; We hope that if the project goes on well it will provide employment to a number of youth in the community who will be providing us with labor, the surrounding farmers will benefit by copying the modern methods which we are going to use on this farm, while the traders will be assured of getting reasonable quantities of produce from the same farm as opposed to collecting the required amounts from all over the parish which has a cost implication, and above all the Church members will be inspired to grow own food through seeing from this farm and they will also get maize for maize floor at a relatively lower price than what other shops charge .
(II) Project goal; To Develop profitable Agro production unit to supply the Domestic market in Uganda and the neighboring countries and to inspire the Christristians around the World to be food secure in their homes.
(III) Project Objective; The project to begin with five acres of Maize grown on well cultivated land, fenced against the cattle presently roaming on the land, with an intention of gradually progressing into a commercial mixed farm growing highly profitable crops as required in the market region to increase in size up to 100 acres out of the available 290 acres.
(IV) Project activities;
We shall start with Bush clearance followed with stump up rooting making the field suitable for Tractor first land preparation First ploughing and second ploughing will be done using hired tractor services. The cleared land will be well fenced using Barbed wire and poles to protect it from stray animals and petty thieves. Planting of maize will follow, observing all the recommended Agronomic practices like; timeliness of operations starting at the end of May 2011 with bush clearance and fine seed bed preparation, use of high yielding seed, hybrid Panar variety, right spacing of (75 cms x 60 cms.), application of a Basal fertilizer before planting which will be followed with top dressing at six weeks. Pest and disease control programs will be strictly observed until the time of harvesting and in storage to minimize post Harvest losses. Post harvest handling will be carefully planned for and carried out to minimize possible losses and the best marketing techniques will be applied to get the best price that will be prevailing at the time. Two seasons will be used to recover some of the preliminary costs and eventually more paying crops like pineapples will be planted where the maize will be harvested on second planting
(v) Project Operations and Management; Richard will be responsible for the first day to day preparatory arrangements with the guidance of a professional consultant, but later the operations will be handed to an experienced farm manager who will be recruited in the course of time.

lender.name: Robert
lender.occupational_info:
I am working as a website developer for a New York Personal Injury Law Firm. NY is reported to be a very busy state and several dangerous accidents validate this. According to the NHSTA, an accident occurs every 10 seconds somewhere in the US due to negligent driving, driving dangerously, or driving under the influence of banned and lethal drugs.
In some accidents, no physical injuries are caused but one can still ask for compensation for physical damages to the car and get the repair expenses, but in accidents where occupants are physically injured then a personal injury lawsuit can be filed against the negligent driver or any other person responsible for the accident/injuries.
Most of the accidents involving heavy vehicles like trucks, tractor-trailers cause serious personal injuries or are fatal to the occupants of the smaller vehicles.
Therefore, if you want justice and right compensation for the injuries, then follow these guidelines :-
a) Ascertain the nature of injuries and damages suffered right after the accident. If anyone is fatally injured including the driver at fault, then ask for medical help right away. Call for an ambulance or the state police at once.
b) File an accident report case in the NY police station and retain a copy of the same. If you are not at fault, then do not admit it. The person responsible for the accident should be handed over to the police.
c) Call a NY car accident lawyer to help in filing an accident injury lawsuit and get compensation for the injuries from negligent individual or authority. If the accident is due to malfunctioning of traffic signals, then a notice can be sent to NY State authorities, as they are responsible for the maintenance of traffic signals.
d) Collect all the essential facts related to the accident like names, address, and the contact numbers of people involved in the accident. Also, write down the car description, license plate number, and vehicle identification number to claim the insurance money.
You may contact New York Personal Injury Lawyers at : The Woolworth Building, 233 Broadway, New York, New York - 10007, Phone : (212) 766-5656
